  "title": "Technician (System Integration)",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Areas of Responsibility</strong></h3><p><br /></p><p>1) Provides technical services including installation & maintenance services on systems, workstations, PC, Lans etc.</p><p>2) Handles customer and channel & sales' queries on service details and work progress.</p><p>3) Performs housekeeping administrative jobs to ensure compliance of internal policies and procedures.</p><p>4) Schedules maintenance jobs based on customer needs and contractual agreements.</p><p>5) Determines usage of parts & labour for repairs and recommend service changes.</p><p>6) Escalate problems as appropriate.</p><p><br /></p><h3>Requirements</h3><p>1) At least a Diploma holder in Electronic Engineering or related fields</p><p>2) Preferably with 1 or 2 years of working experience</p><p>3) Able to work in a team</p><p>4) Bilingual in English & Mandarin due to requirements to communicate with our Taiwan HQ.</p>",
